<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="424" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,509,681]" pageId="7" pageNumber="424">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Jelinek, J. &amp; Audisio, P." box="[358,671,582,608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="424" refId="ref5731" refString="Jelinek, J. &amp; Audisio, P. (2007) Nitidulidae. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 4. Elateroidea - Derodontoidea - Bostrichoidea - Lymexyloidea - Cleroidea - Cucujoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 476 - 477." type="book" year="2007">Jelinek and Audisio (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, this common and widespread species is mainly distributed across Europe, 
<collectingCountry box="[245,320,618,644]" name="Russia" pageId="7" pageNumber="424">Russia</collectingCountry>
(Far East and west Siberia), 
<collectingCountry box="[640,711,618,644]" name="South Korea" pageId="7" pageNumber="424">Korea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[722,789,618,644]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="424">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[799,908,618,644]" name="Mongolia" pageId="7" pageNumber="424">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
and North American (
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk, A. G." box="[1155,1341,618,644]" pageId="7" pageNumber="424" pagination="114 - 209" refId="ref5884" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. (1992) 59., 61. Sem. Nitidulidae-Blestyanki. In: Ler, P. A. (Ed.), Opredelitel'nasekomykh Dal'nego Vostoka SSSR v shesti tomakh. Tom III. Zhestkokrylye, ili zhuki. Nauka, Sankt-Petersburg, pp. 114 - 209." type="book chapter" year="1992">Kirejtshuk 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Here it is reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[339,406,654,680]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="424">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[420,599,654,681]" country="China" name="Nei Mongol" pageId="7" pageNumber="424">Inner Mongolia</collectingRegion>
) for the first time.
</paragraph>
